# Radial Tuberosity

> The **radial tuberosity** (bicipital tuberosity) is a roughened oval prominence just distal to the radial head on the anteromedial [[Radius]], where the [[Biceps Brachii]] tendon inserts.

## 🔗 Key Connections
- [[Radius]] — proximal radius, distal to the radial head
- [[Biceps Brachii]] — inserts here via the biceps tendon (flexion + supination)

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **Distal biceps tendon rupture** — Avulsion at radial tuberosity; "popeye" deformity, weak supination
- **Surgical repair** — Reattachment to radial tuberosity restores supination strength

## 📍 Location
[[Skeletal System]] → [[Radius]] → Radial Tuberosity
